						<summary>

						<p>On the fourth pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 32: 938-39 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This mutilated inscription seems to record a gift of sheep for burning a perpetual lamp for the merit of Kaḍambaṉ Eḻuvaṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
